text: Kim Hye-mi (born 16 April 1983) is a South Korean taekwondo practitioner. She won a gold medal in welterweight at the 2001 World Taekwondo Championships, and a gold medal at the 2002 Asian Taekwondo Championships. ==References== ==External links== * Category:1983 births Category:Living people Category:South Korean female taekwondo practitioners Category:World Taekwondo Championships medalists Category:Asian Taekwondo Championships medalists
